cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this software, please cite it as below."
type: software
title: "Pulpit: Political undercurrents — linkage, propagation, influence on Telegram"
authors:
  - family-names: Baldini
    given-names: Giovanni
    email: giovanni.baldini@gmail.com
version: "0.18"
date-released: "2026-05-10"
repository-code: "https://github.com/giovabal/pulpit"
license: GPL-3.0-only
abstract: >-
  Pulpit crawls a user-defined set of Telegram channels, traces every forward
  and every t.me/ cross-reference between them, and turns the result into an
  interactive network map. It applies established methods from network science —
  PageRank, HITS, Burt's structural holes, Leiden and Infomap community
  detection, SIR spreading simulation, and more — to map influence, information
  flow, and community structure in Telegram forwarding networks.
keywords:
  - Telegram
  - social network analysis
  - community detection
  - information operations
  - disinformation research
  - political communication
  - influence mapping
  - graph visualization
  - computational social science
  - network science
